      <bioghist id="aspace_190d2ac4d11b9d7776e73bea4240fc64">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Dodsley's Collection was founded by Wilmarth S. Lewis and Herman W. Liebert in 1950. It served as a dining club for scholars from Yale to recite and discuss 18th century works. It met once a year until 1980.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <arrangement id="aspace_32c28599d91aab67610d6b118e749266">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The collection is arranged by type of material.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_cf15f8a844a436e5c5a26dffd3fc75a0">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of member lists, correspondence, essays, and papers documenting Dodsley's Collection at Yale. Among the records is a paper that discusses the derivation of the club's name.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
